.TH "IXALANCE" "1" "June 2026" "ixalance 1.0.6" "User Commands"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
ixalance \[em] DOS32 demo loader for Linux (The Black Lotus demo system)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]ixalance\f[R] [\f[I]OPTIONS\f[R]] \f[I]demo.ixa\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]ixalance\f[R] is a DOS32 protected-mode demo loader for Linux.
It was originally written by Jurjen Katsman (The Black Lotus, TBL) and
ported to Linux and SDL by Jarno Paananen.
.PP
It runs TBL demo files (\f[B].ixa\f[R] archives) by emulating the 32-bit
protected-mode environment the demos expect, while rendering graphics
through SDL2 and playing music through libopenmpt and SDL2 audio.
.PP
The program opens a resizable SDL2 window at the native resolution of
each demo effect (typically 320×200, 640×480, or 800×600) and scales it
to fill the window while preserving the original aspect ratio.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-m\f[R]\f[I]x\f[R]
Set the audio mixing rate to \f[I]x\f[R] Hz (e.g.\ \f[B]-m44100\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]-o\f[R]\f[I]x\f[R]
Set the output mode.
Valid values: \f[B]8\f[R] (8-bit), \f[B]1\f[R] (16-bit), \f[B]s\f[R]
(stereo), \f[B]m\f[R] (mono).
.TP
\f[B]-f\f[R]\f[I]x\f[R]
Set the interpolation filter.
Valid values: \f[B]0\f[R] (none), \f[B]1\f[R] (less), \f[B]2\f[R]
(more).
.TP
\f[B]-i\f[R]
Enable oversampling (interpolation).
.TP
\f[B]-s\f[R]\f[I]W\f[R]\f[B]x\f[R]\f[I]H\f[R]
Force the initial window size to \f[I]W\f[R]×\f[I]H\f[R] pixels
(e.g.\ \f[B]-s800x600\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]-d\f[R]
Write debugging output to \f[B]debug.txt\f[R] in the current directory.
.TP
\f[B]-t\f[R]
Print frames per second to standard output.
.TP
\f[B]-F\f[R]
Start in fullscreen mode.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
\f[B]F\f[R]
Toggle fullscreen / windowed mode at any time during playback.
Fullscreen uses \f[B]SDL_WINDOW_FULLSCREEN_DESKTOP\f[R] so the desktop
resolution is preserved; the demo image is centred and letter-boxed to
maintain the correct aspect ratio.
.TP
\f[B]ESC\f[R]
Quit the program cleanly.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]debug.txt\f[R]
Debug log written in the current working directory when \f[B]-d\f[R] is
used.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Normal exit (demo finished or user pressed \f[B]ESC\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Error (missing or unreadable demo file, SDL initialisation failure,
etc.).
.SH BUGS
.PP
The program only runs \f[B].ixa\f[R] archives produced by The Black
Lotus demo system; it is not a general-purpose DOS emulator.
.PP
Code compiled from \f[B]code.asm\f[R] is i386 protected-mode only; the
binary must be built as a 32-bit ELF executable (\f[B]-m32\f[R]).
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]sdl2-config\f[R](1)
.PP
Upstream iXalance/Linux home page: <http://www.s2.org/iXalance/>
.PP
TBL demo archive: <http://www.tbl.org/tbl32.htm>
.SH AUTHORS
.PP
